-- European Union Carbon Permits for 2012 Rise to Two-Week High
-- B y   E w a   K r u k o w s k a
-- 2012-09-27T16:14:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-27/european-union-carbon-permits-for-2012-rise-to-two-week-high.html
European Union carbon permits for
delivery in December advanced to the highest level in almost two
weeks.  The contract added as much as 3.5 percent to 7.90 euros a
metric ton on the ICE Futures Europe exchange in  London , the
highest since Sept. 14. Permits were at 7.85 euros a ton as of
5:09 p.m. local time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ewa Krukowska in Brussels at 
 ekrukowska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
